⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Fighter
node TGL · TGL · ⟦The Fighter:TGL:a5461a⟧

WHO   — The Fighter — the star-fighter form
WHAT  — The shoot-'em-up half of The Guardian Legend — the form in which the top-down adventure becomes a vertical-scrolling barrage, the Guardian flying the Corridors as a ship of war.
WHERE — TGL · The Guardian Legend  Framework inputs: The Guardian Legend (Compile, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because some passages of an alien world cannot be walked, only flown and fought through; because the Guardian was built to be both explorer and weapon; because to clear a Corridor you must stop being a maiden and start being a gun.
HOW   — By transformation at the mouth of each Corridor — maiden folding into craft — and by the rain of fire that follows, threading enemy bullets at speed until the boss that seals the way falls.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  When the corridor opens, the maiden folds away — and what flies in is all guns.

